# Core Module Specific Standards

> **Related Rules**: See [Architecture Standards](./architecture.mdc), [Security Standards](./security.mdc), [Error Handling](./error-handling.mdc)

## HTTP Interceptors

- Authentication interceptor for adding tokens
- Error interceptor for global error handling
- Logging interceptor for request/response logging
- Use functional interceptors (Angular 20+)

## Internationalization Services

- i18n service for translations
- Support multiple languages
- Lazy load translations
- Use ng-alain i18n integration

## Route Guards

- Authentication guard
- Authorization guard
- Unsaved changes guard
- Use functional guards (Angular 20+)

## Singleton Services

- All services in core/ are singletons
- Provide in root: `providedIn: 'root'`
- Must be stateless or manage global state
- No component-specific logic

